Determined to provide portable and adequate water supply to the rural areas in the state, Gombe State government said over 250 handpump boreholes had been repaired and are functioning in the rural areas of the state. Commissioner for Water Resources, Mijinyawa Yahaya, disclosed this in an exclusive interview with LEADERSHIP in Gombe. He equally said generators and diesel are also provided, to ensure the boreholes provide enough and uninterrupted water supply to the rural folks. Yahaya added that, “we will ensure the rehabilitation of more boreholes, and new ones are to be sunk to ensure all the rural areas in the state get portable water supply.”   He expressed optimism in getting 660 handpump boreholes repaired, noting than loans will also be secured from ADB. The commissioner further told LEADERSHIP that the state government, has the political will to tackle headlong, all challenges associated with water supply in the state. While disclosing that the immediate past government owed major water contractors huge amount of money, Yahaya also noted that Governor Inuwa Yahaya’s administration have been paying N250 million monthly to offset the debt. The commissioner, however assured’ the people of the state that the state government will continue to work hard, with a view to ensuring it delivers democracy dividends to them. 